==English==

===Noun===

'''[[geostrophic]] wind level'''

# ([[Meteorology]]). The lowest level at which the wind becomes [[geostrophic]]. In practice, the geostrophic wind level is between 1.2 [[kilometers]] (3,928 [[feet]]) and 1.6 kilometers (5,238 feet). This wind level probably marks the upper limit of [[frictional influence]] of the earth's surface. The geostrophic wind level may be considered to be the top of the [[planetary boundary layer]], that is, the base of the [[free atmosphere]]. Also known as '''''gradient wind level'''''.

